 J.|title=Technology and the Mid-Victorian Royal Navy Ironclad: Royal Navy Crisis in the Age of Palmerston|publisher=Routledge|year= 2014|ref=harv}} [https://www.amazon.com/Empire-Technology-Seapower-Palmerston-History/dp/0415370043/ Excerpt]\n* Henderson, Gavin B. \"The Foreign Policy of Lord Palmerston\" ''History'' 22#88 (1938), pp. 335-344, [https://www.jstor.org/stable/24401363 online]\n* {{cite book|last=Hicks|first= Geoffrey|title=Peace, War and party politics: the Conservatives and Europe, 1846\u201359|publisher=Manchester University Press|year=2007|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last=Hoppen|first= K. Theodore|title=The Mid-Victorian Generation, 1846\u20131886|year=1998|ref=harv}}, wide-ranging scholarly survey\n* Leonard, Dick ''Nineteenth Century British Premieres: Pitt to Roseberry'' (2008) pp 245\u201365.\n* Macknight, Thomas. ''Thirty Years of Foreign Policy, a History of the Secretaryships of the Earl of Aberdeen and Viscount Palmerston'' (1855),  [https://archive.org/details/thirtyyearsoffor00mackrich/page/n6 Online free]\n* {{cite book|last=Martin|first= Kingsley|title=The Triumph of Lord Palmerston: a study of public opinion in England before the Crimean War|url=https://archive.org/details/triumphoflordpal0000mart|url-access=registration|year=1963|ref=harv}} [https://archive.org/details/in.ernet.dli.2015.191245 Online free]\n* Paul, Herbert. ''History of Modern England'', 1904-6 (5 vols) [https://archive.org/details/historyofmoderne02paul <!-- quote=intitle:History intitle:of intitle:Modern intitle:England inauthor:herbert inauthor:paul. --> vol 2 online] 1855\u20131865\n* {{cite book|last=Ridley|first= Jasper|title=Lord Palmerston|place=London|publisher=Constable|year=1970|ref=harv}}; [https://archive.org/details/lordpalmerston00ridl Online free to borrow] \n* Seton-Watson, R. W. ''Britain in Europe, 1789\u20131914: A survey of foreign policy'' (1937) pp 241\u2013300, 400\u201363.\n* {{cite book|first=Donald|last= Southgate|title='The Most English Minis