ace=London|publisher= Victor Gollancz|date=1928|url=https://www.questia.com/library/3254346/gladstone-and-palmerston-being-the-correspondence|ref=harv}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikiquote}}\n* {{Hansard-contribs | viscount-palmerston | Viscount Palmerston }}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20100808092206/http://www.liberalhistory.org.uk/item_single.php?item_id=13&item=biography Viscount Palmerston 1784\u20131865] biography from the Liberal Democrat History Group\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20070420212652/http://www.pm.gov.uk/output/Page149.asp More about Viscount Palmerston] on the Downing Street website.\n* {{Cite EB1911|wstitle=Palmerston, Henry John Temple, 3rd Viscount}}\n* {{UK National Archives ID}}\n* [http://www.southampton.ac.uk/archives/cataloguedatabases/palm/index.page Papers of Henry John Temple, third Viscount Palmerston]. University of Southampton.\n* {{NPG name}}\n*[http://www.edwardjdavies.info/PMs/temple.htm Edward J. Davies, \u201cThe Ancestry of Lord Palmerston\u201d, The Genealogist, 22(2008):62\u201377]\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-off}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Granville Leveson-Gower, 1st Earl Granville|Lord Granville Leveson-Gower]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Secretary at War]]|years=1809\u20131828}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Henry Hardinge, 1st Viscount Hardinge|Sir Henry Hardinge]]}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[George Hamilton-Gordon, 4th Earl of Aberdeen|The Earl of Aberdeen]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Secretary of State for Foreign Affairs|Foreign Secretary]]|years=1830\u20131834}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Arthur Wellesley, 1st Duke of Wellington|The Duke of Wellington]]}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Arthur Wellesley, 1st Duke of Wellington|The Duke of Wellington]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Secretary of State for Foreign Affairs|Foreign Secretary]]|years=1835\u20131841}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[George Hamilton-Gordon, 4th Earl of Aberdeen|The Earl of Aberdeen]]}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[George Hamilton-Gordon, 4th Earl of Aberdeen|The Earl of Aberdeen]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Secretary of State for Foreign Affairs|Foreign Sec